20:15.414 --> 20:21.920
Jesus prays in John chapter 14 that he will send a helper that will be with us, he will be with us forever.

20:22.340 --> 20:29.106
So we have a very different and far better, by the way, relationship with the spirit than those in the Old Testament did.

20:29.406 --> 20:40.676
But that idea of indwelling and regeneration and a permanent ceiling of the spirit, that is a New Testament concept that you and I certainly enjoy and love, but that wasn't necessarily understood.

20:40.656 --> 20:43.099
in the Old Testament in the same way.

20:43.620 --> 20:51.611
So as you think about Saul's life, his experience with the Holy Spirit would be very different than yours in mine.

20:52.532 --> 20:54.695
Now again, he has an epic start.

20:55.115 --> 21:09.074
He's anointed by Samuel to understand the spirits coming upon him in a mighty way that is a powerful and wonderful thing that we absolutely celebrate because God is enabling him to do something that otherwise he couldn't do.

21:09.698 --> 21:16.405
And by the way, as we look at the rest of chapter 10, Saul is now going to be publicly presented before the people as their king.

21:16.485 --> 21:22.312
Look down at verse 21, and let's watch now this kind of inauguration ceremony of Saul.

21:23.293 --> 21:27.037
It says they brought the tribe of Benjamin nearby its families.

21:27.097 --> 21:28.078
This is Saul's family.

21:28.819 --> 21:30.441
The matriarch family then was taken.

21:31.262 --> 21:35.346
And then Saul, the son of Kish was taken, but when they looked for him,

21:35.906 --> 21:37.149
he could not be found.

21:37.489 --> 21:45.526
They are ready to publicly affirm Saul as their king and they can't find him at his very own inauguration ceremony.

21:45.546 --> 21:50.116
Verse 22, it says, therefore they required further the Lord saying, has he come here yet?

21:50.336 --> 21:51.238
Like is he around?

21:51.278 --> 21:52.300
Has anybody seen him?

21:52.360 --> 21:57.010
And the Lord said, behold, he is hiding himself in the baggage.

21:57.250 --> 21:58.772
Maybe out of fear, right?

21:58.792 --> 21:59.553
That's a big day.

22:00.094 --> 22:11.590
Maybe out of a genuine humility or a lack of yearning for the spotlight, Saul has to be drug out behind the baggage to now be presented before the people, which is exactly what happens in verse 24.

22:12.952 --> 22:18.479
Samuel said to all the people, do you see him whom the Lord has chosen?

22:19.100 --> 22:21.964
Surely there is no one like him among all the people.

22:22.404 --> 22:26.450
So all the people shouted and said, long live the king.

22:27.202 --> 22:29.605
Same as says, this is the guy you asked for.

22:29.905 --> 22:30.185
Yes?

22:30.826 --> 22:31.186
Okay.

22:32.047 --> 22:34.290
There's nobody else like him in all of Israel.

22:34.330 --> 22:34.570
Yes?

22:34.670 --> 22:35.351
That's our guy.

22:35.611 --> 22:38.334
And they say, long live the king, right?

22:38.655 --> 22:40.557
At least most of them.

22:41.358 --> 22:42.659
Look down at verse 27.

22:43.500 --> 22:49.046
But certain worthless men said, how can this one deliver us?

22:49.627 --> 22:54.893
And they despised him and did not bring him any present.

22:54.913 --> 22:55.954
But he kept silent.

22:56.354 --> 23:02.284
So Saul in his very inauguration day has people on the other side of the aisle that said, well, we didn't vote for this guy.

23:02.324 --> 23:08.254
We're not going to affirm him that now kind of blast him publicly, embarrass him maybe in a lot of ways.

23:08.755 --> 23:11.159
And Saul says, nothing.

23:11.660 --> 23:14.465
He holds his tongue in that moment.

23:14.645 --> 23:19.213
It's a beautiful quality, actually, where he doesn't revile when he's been reviled.

23:19.654 --> 23:22.098
So he's certainly not a fan of everybody.

23:22.178 --> 23:26.444
But initially, as we see Saul's life, he has rocket ship success.

23:27.005 --> 23:29.930
A couple of days ago, he's a nobody looking for some lost donkeys.

23:30.310 --> 23:33.835
And now, he is the king of the nation of Israel.

23:33.915 --> 23:35.257
God's chosen nation.

23:35.458 --> 23:39.303
And remember, why did the people choose Saul?

23:39.985 --> 23:44.171
We want a guy who can go out and fight our battles.

23:44.792 --> 23:46.694
See also now, chapter 11.

23:47.536 --> 23:48.517
Look at verses one and two.

23:50.480 --> 23:51.762
It says, now,

23:52.034 --> 23:53.716
The king of the Ammonites.

23:53.736 --> 23:56.799
This is a pagan nation east of Israel.

23:57.180 --> 24:02.265
It says, this guy came up against in besieged J.Besh Gilead, one of the cities within Israel.

24:02.706 --> 24:06.870
And all the men of J.Besh said now to Nahash, make a covenant with us.

24:07.110 --> 24:07.911
We will serve you.

24:08.412 --> 24:11.896
But Nahash, the Ammonite said to them, I'll make a covenant with you on this condition.

24:12.396 --> 24:14.979
How about I gouge out the right eye of every one of you?

24:15.219 --> 24:17.682
Thus I will make it an approach in all of Israel.

24:18.114 --> 24:22.498
So part of Israel, this city on the east side of the Jordan River is attacked by this pagan king.

24:22.779 --> 24:27.683
They're literally on an island and they realize there's nobody here to come help us.

24:28.104 --> 24:31.227
So they kind of give into this king and say, look, well, let's make a covenant with you.

24:31.247 --> 24:31.988
Stop the battle.

24:32.408 --> 24:35.932
In Nahash, whose name needs snake, by the way, he's not a very nice guy.

24:36.212 --> 24:37.313
He says, I got a covenant for you.

24:37.333 --> 24:38.814
How about I stab out all your right eyes?

24:38.834 --> 24:39.595
You like that covenant?

24:40.036 --> 24:41.477
And they say, well, maybe not so much.

24:42.118 --> 24:44.240
They said, hey, how about you give us a week?

24:45.080 --> 24:46.642
And we send out a distress signal.

24:46.978 --> 24:51.263
And if nobody comes to rescue us in a week, we will submit to you.

24:51.483 --> 24:52.404
You do whatever you want.

24:52.785 --> 24:54.426
So that is their request in verse three.

24:54.607 --> 24:58.731
Let us alone, seven days, that we may send messengers throughout all of Israel.

24:59.072 --> 25:01.915
If no one comes to deliver us, we will come out to you.

25:02.435 --> 25:08.042
Well, this word reaches the people of Israel that part of their brothers have been attacked.

25:08.442 --> 25:11.245
They weep and Saul finds out as well.

25:11.365 --> 25:12.627
Look at verse six.

25:13.948 --> 25:15.410
Then the spirit of God

25:15.618 --> 25:22.028
came upon Saul mightily when he heard these words and he became angry.

25:22.048 --> 25:28.638
Once again, empowered by God, now to deliver his people, Saul rallies a country to fight.

25:28.658 --> 25:29.660
Look at verse seven.

25:30.361 --> 25:43.922
He took a yoke of oxen, cut them in pieces, and sent them throughout the territory of Israel by the hand of messenger saying, whoever does not come out after Saul and after Samuel, so it shall be done to his oxen.

25:44.226 --> 25:49.117
Then the dread of the Lord fell upon the people and they came out as one man.

25:50.019 --> 25:52.184
What an odd FedEx package to get.

25:53.206 --> 25:56.353
And Saul says, listen, hear these words.

25:57.034 --> 26:02.707
If you don't want to happen to your oxen, what happened to these oxen, then y'all better show up to battle.

26:03.068 --> 26:04.210
We got some people.

26:04.290 --> 26:08.074
our brothers that are in need and we're gonna come rescue them.

26:08.454 --> 26:14.841
And by the way, verse eight tells us, Saul rallies a army of 330,000 strong.

26:15.342 --> 26:19.346
And he tells the people of J. Beshgili, y'all hang on, we're coming.

26:19.726 --> 26:24.751
And in verse 11, it says, the next morning, Saul put the people into three companies.

26:25.332 --> 26:31.058
They came into the midst of the camp in the morning watch and struck down the Ammonites until the heat

26:31.170 --> 26:36.257
of the day and those who survived were scattered so that no two of them were left together.

26:36.818 --> 26:40.924
Saul comes in as king and he leads strong.

26:41.485 --> 26:48.455
Not by the way, just as a warrior, which is what they expected, but he leads as a general, dividing the people into three different companies.

26:48.695 --> 26:50.217
He's got strategy behind this.

26:50.418 --> 26:59.090
He rallies these people and they fight from dawn all the way to the heat of the day towards sunset and they obliterate this pagan king.

26:59.426 --> 27:03.293
And they rescue Israel from this man's hand.

27:03.794 --> 27:08.743
And it says in verse 14 and 15, as Saul unites a nation.

27:09.364 --> 27:14.613
Samuel said to the people, come let us go down to Gilgal and renew the kingdom there.

27:15.335 --> 27:17.298
So all the people went to Gilgal.

27:17.570 --> 27:21.776
And there they made Saul king before the Lord in Gilgal.

27:21.796 --> 27:24.940
They offered sacrifices, peace offerings before the Lord.

27:25.281 --> 27:29.426
And there Saul and all the men of Israel rejoiced greatly.

27:29.947 --> 27:32.851
This is Saul's bright shining moment.

27:33.132 --> 27:34.493
He leads strong.

27:34.534 --> 27:36.136
The people say yes in amen.

27:36.536 --> 27:38.239
Saul, it's exactly why we picked you.

27:38.279 --> 27:39.380
We knew you could do it.

27:39.881 --> 27:44.287
In a lot of ways, they're saying to the Lord, we told you so.

27:45.409 --> 27:46.450
We needed a king.

27:46.658 --> 27:53.689
just like this, because those nahashes out there, those pagan kings, they're coming, and we don't have a king to rescue us.

27:54.049 --> 27:56.292
And Saul did exactly what we asked for.

27:56.753 --> 27:59.758
We told you, God, that's exactly what we needed.

27:59.778 --> 28:04.525
So they celebrate and they look very justified in their own eyes.

28:05.486 --> 28:16.082
And then now, after this public parade, the celebration of this victory lap that Saul's doing, it says, the people said to Samuel, hey, where are those guys?

28:16.354 --> 28:24.542
that we're talking smack at Saul's original inauguration that said, hey, we didn't vote for this guy, boo, he can't do the job.

28:24.802 --> 28:30.628
He said, why don't we bring those guys out that we may put them to death in verse 12.

28:31.649 --> 28:37.094
And Saul says in verse 13, not a man shall be put to death this day.

28:37.755 --> 28:40.958
For the Lord has accomplished deliverance in Israel.

28:41.879 --> 28:43.260
What an amazing quality.

28:43.841 --> 28:44.882
Saul had the right

28:45.154 --> 28:53.602
And Saul had the ability as king to snap his fingers and say, off with their heads, how dare those guys mock me publicly.

28:54.103 --> 28:54.864
But Saul says, you know what?

28:54.904 --> 28:55.765
No, not today.

28:55.785 --> 28:57.667
Not because I won a battle.

28:57.687 --> 28:58.247
Did you see it?

28:58.868 --> 29:02.271
The Lord has accomplished deliverance in Israel.

29:02.551 --> 29:06.295
And he says, we're not going to take away from that moment to deal with these knuckleheads.

29:07.056 --> 29:08.437
And Saul holds his peace.

29:08.998 --> 29:13.202
It took maturity and wisdom to not give in in that moment.

29:13.602 --> 29:22.114
So as we see these first three chapters into Saul's reign as king, all looks great above the surface.

29:22.134 --> 29:23.916
In fact, there's more to come.

29:24.417 --> 29:27.481
More things about Saul that you will no doubt admire and like.

29:28.102 --> 29:32.087
At the very least, this far into the journey, we see a man chosen by God.

29:32.628 --> 29:35.833
He comes from what certainly seems to be a very solid family.

29:36.474 --> 29:38.797
He's respectful, honors older men.

29:38.857 --> 29:42.642
He's obedient and listens to what Samuel tells him so far.

29:42.786 --> 29:43.747
He's humble.

29:44.267 --> 29:46.510
He doesn't have an over-inflated view of himself.

29:46.970 --> 29:48.051
And he's magnanimous.

29:48.471 --> 29:52.535
He rises above the kind of the naysayers around him and says, you know what?

29:52.595 --> 29:54.117
I don't have to respond in kind.

29:54.557 --> 29:58.441
I can be mature and wise in how I deal with others.

29:58.701 --> 30:00.443
These are all qualities as parents.

30:00.463 --> 30:02.465
We would say we would love to see these in our kids.

30:03.025 --> 30:04.667
These are all qualities if we're honest.

30:05.167 --> 30:07.890
We want to see in our political rulers today.

30:07.950 --> 30:12.434
They're beautiful things that we appreciate years and years later.

30:13.250 --> 30:21.923
And though Saul starts so well, the vast majority of his reign is gonna be marked by poor leadership.

30:23.105 --> 30:23.665
What happened?

30:24.647 --> 30:34.502
What's lurking underneath the surface that we don't fully see yet, but we're seeing inklings, cracks, the beginnings of things that we need to consider.

30:35.082 --> 30:40.210
If I could offer maybe three things that are happening in the life of Saul that are both true of him,

30:40.418 --> 30:46.465
in both true of us at the same time regarding these matters when we peer underneath the surface.

30:47.386 --> 30:48.808
Things that certainly will lead to doom.

30:48.848 --> 30:54.034
Number one, when responsibility exceeds character.

30:55.115 --> 31:03.144
Saul's gonna be put in a very difficult situation where the external growth exceeds the growth of what's happening underneath.

31:03.545 --> 31:07.890
That's the problem with overnight rocket ship success.

31:08.226 --> 31:12.031
Days ago, Saul's a nobody looking for his donkeys and again, today he's king of Israel.

31:12.732 --> 31:19.340
Nobody wants that type of fame immediately overnight because the insides can't keep up with the outsides.

31:19.921 --> 31:22.504
He's gonna be a flash in the pan type of spirituality.

31:22.524 --> 31:23.465
He's lighter fluid.

31:23.866 --> 31:28.552
It burns hot, it burns fast, but when it's gone, it's gone.

31:30.194 --> 31:31.956
In Texas, we have a saying for a guy like that.

31:32.517 --> 31:33.999
We say he's all hat and no cattle.

31:35.080 --> 31:36.562
That's kind of Saul's life.

31:36.866 --> 31:40.309
And though his leadership starts strong, again, those cracks are evident.

31:40.750 --> 31:52.721
Gene Edwards in his book, A Tale of Three Kings About King Saul and a couple others, he says this, outward power will always reveal the inner resources or lack thereof.

31:53.402 --> 31:55.704
And that's what's coming in the life of Saul.

31:55.724 --> 31:57.726
If I'm honest, I have a bit of sympathy for Saul.

31:57.886 --> 32:06.034
As much as it's tempting to envy that position and say, oh, wouldn't it be great to be the king and enjoy all the accolades that come with that, I feel bad for him.

32:06.498 --> 32:10.383
because he was put in a position that he never should have been in.

32:10.724 --> 32:16.392
He did not have the character to sustain what the people have asked him to do.

32:16.832 --> 32:22.480
And the problem is, once he has tasted kingship, he will not let go of it.

32:23.622 --> 32:26.506
So secondly, things that lead to demise.

32:26.926 --> 32:32.434
When you get too big for your britches, I'm gonna bring that word britches back into Arlingo.

32:33.218 --> 32:40.448
Saul's just read too much of his own press, that early humility that we see and love about him, it simply doesn't last.

32:41.190 --> 32:44.675
He began now to disregard God's hand and his appointment as king.

32:45.055 --> 32:50.824
He's gonna become prideful and arrogant, close his heart to the Lord and begin to do things his own way.

32:51.364 --> 32:56.932
And what's even more disturbing about it is he's above everybody and nobody is able to rebuke him.

32:57.433 --> 33:00.818
No one's able to say, hey, Saul, that's not a great idea.

33:01.058 --> 33:03.902
Or hey, Saul, I don't think God's honored in that.

33:04.302 --> 33:06.005
Would you consider this instead?

33:06.065 --> 33:09.109
Or would you stop and repent and turn to the Lord?

33:09.409 --> 33:11.793
He never will acknowledge his own sin.

33:12.233 --> 33:18.622
He always points fingers, says it's that person's fault or whoever it may be, but he will never own his own junk.

33:18.662 --> 33:22.627
And it's devastating to see him read too much of his own press.

33:23.148 --> 33:30.418
And then lastly, when we stop cultivating our inner worlds, one of the most

33:30.818 --> 33:47.096
challenging things to see with Saul that's just heartbreaking is that in the areas that nobody else sees, Saul is unwilling to do the work below the waterline underneath the surface, that deep abiding relationship with the Lord is absent in Saul.

33:47.937 --> 33:49.319
Brad calls it the lonely work.

33:50.140 --> 33:59.570
The things that you do to cultivate your relationship with God, that nobody else around you sees, they don't get praised, they don't get accolades,

33:59.650 --> 34:10.300
You don't get medals for spending time with the Lord and being open to His work in your life, but those things matter because they sustain everything else above the surface.

34:10.320 --> 34:13.203
Saul's issue, by the way, will not be for lack of effort.

34:13.563 --> 34:15.745
He works hard as a king.

34:15.785 --> 34:20.370
His issue will be for lack of cultivation of His inner world.

34:20.950 --> 34:22.952
That is what will lead to His demise.

34:22.972 --> 34:26.315
And these symptoms will become more and more evident.

34:26.956 --> 34:29.298
And so one day, there's a sinkhole.

34:29.858 --> 34:32.582
and everything simply collapses in his life.

34:33.122 --> 34:35.525
It's gonna feel like it happens overnight.

34:36.146 --> 34:44.377
And yet as we peer again underneath the surface in his life, we realize that there are signs and symptoms happening that lead to this demise.

34:44.777 --> 34:51.226
And again, he will reign in Israel for 40 years as a king that does not have a heart for the Lord.

34:52.287 --> 34:54.610
Now there's a temptation, I think in all of us,

34:54.722 --> 35:02.253
to move as we see Saul's life to a place of moralism and say, hey, the lesson here is don't be like Saul.

35:02.433 --> 35:04.276
And that's, by the way, not a terrible lesson.

35:04.817 --> 35:10.325
In fact, Paul tells the church at Corinth regarding the Old Testament and the stories that we have.

35:10.685 --> 35:15.993
He says these things happen to them as an example and they were written for our instruction.

35:16.073 --> 35:19.698
We need to see the life of Saul and say, hey, that maybe isn't the best

35:20.002 --> 35:21.083
best path to take.

35:21.384 --> 35:25.990
There's a lot of wisdom in avoiding what Paul, or sorry, what Saul here is going to do.

35:26.570 --> 35:33.760
But I think what's maybe more telling for us and maybe a greater lesson is to say that there's a whole lot of Saul that still resides in me.

35:34.360 --> 35:38.085
And walking in the flesh is much easier than walking in the Spirit.

35:38.446 --> 35:42.991
It is weird and awkward and a new thing that I have to learn through the Spirit's empowerment.

35:43.011 --> 35:48.178
And as a man who's in dwell with the Holy Spirit, I still have temptations and

35:48.258 --> 35:56.930
tendencies to walk in a manner of life that is very familiar to me, and to pursue things that don't honor the Lord, just like Saul did.

35:56.990 --> 36:05.301
And yet, I'm indwelt by the Holy Spirit, abiding in the Spirit is awkward, and it's hard at times as we learn how to do that.

36:05.842 --> 36:10.629
And trying harder is not the answer, abiding with the Lord is.

36:11.330 --> 36:17.298
So maybe as we conclude today, something to think about is asking ourselves the question, are we cultivating

36:17.538 --> 36:24.230
that inner person through God's word, through God's spirit, through God's people, specifically in this regard to the spirit.

36:24.491 --> 36:26.815
Are we open to Him and His work in our lives?

36:27.296 --> 36:42.002
You see, the beauty of where we stand now is New Testament believers, as that we have the spirit inside of us, and we get to enjoy His slow, intentional, purposeful work in our inner worlds over the long haul.

36:42.306 --> 36:52.842
And though we don't maybe see the big flash in the pan, spiritual moments like Saul does when the spirit of God comes upon him mightily, I would argue what we have is so much better because he is with us.

36:53.263 --> 36:59.853
For those of us who have embraced the gospel and he will never lead us and he promises to lead us into all truth.

37:00.294 --> 37:05.642
If we will walk with him and stay open to him and allow him to empower our lives.

37:06.122 --> 37:11.090
So as we think about maybe this lesson from the life of Saul, would we be those that are open

37:11.426 --> 37:18.813
to the Spirit's work and actions and leadings and empowerment in our lives for His good and His glory.

37:19.994 --> 37:34.668
Father, thank You for these stories that You have captured for us, that we can see the lessons that we're to learn, but God, more than anything that they would drive us to You, that we would be mindful that like Saul, we can do nothing apart from Your work in our life.

37:35.028 --> 37:41.234
And Father, we cannot live the Christian life without the empowerment of Your Spirit,

37:41.538 --> 37:48.008
But God, there's a constant battle between our old nature, our flesh, and the Holy Spirit that indwells us.

37:49.049 --> 37:51.833
God, that battle is ever-present, and will be until we die.

37:52.414 --> 38:00.105
So would we be those who choose to walk in the Spirit, to acknowledge your power and your presence, to deny the works of our flesh, God, and to walk with you?

38:00.506 --> 38:07.016
Father, would you help us in that journey as we submit to you and desire to please you in our lives in all things?

38:07.496 --> 38:08.177
Would you be honored?

38:08.197 --> 38:08.858
Father, we love you.

38:08.958 --> 38:10.180
We thank you for Christ's name.

38:10.220 --> 38:10.561
We pray.

38:11.122 --> 38:11.442
Amen.

